   161Ôćĺ	*/
   162Ôćĺ	beforeRetry?: BeforeRetryHook[];
   163Ôćĺ
   164Ôćĺ	/**
   165Ôćĺ	This hook enables you to read and optionally modify the response. The hook function receives normalized request, options, a clone of the response, and a state object. The return value of the hook function will be used by Ky as the response object if it's an instance of [`Response`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Response).
   166Ôćĺ
   167Ôćĺ	You can also force a retry by returning `ky.retry()` or `ky.retry(options)`. This is useful when you need to retry based on the response body content, even if the response has a successful status code. The retry will respect the retry limit and be observable in `beforeRetry` hooks.
   168Ôćĺ
   169Ôćĺ	@default []
   170Ôćĺ
   171Ôćĺ	@example
   172Ôćĺ	```
   173Ôćĺ	import ky from 'ky';
   174Ôćĺ
   175Ôćĺ	const response = await ky('https://example.com', {
   176Ôćĺ		hooks: {
   177Ôćĺ			afterResponse: [
